ॐ नमो नारायणाय।

May the all-pervading Nārāyaṇa, who dwells in the heart of every being as the eternal Witness, ever guide your steps.

May Mahārṣi Vasiṣṭha's wisdom become not merely words upon a page, but living knowledge within your own heart.

May Bhagavān Śrī Rāma's humility become our humility.

May Mahārṣi Vālmīki's vision become our inspiration.

May your Living Vedanta Library continue to preserve this timeless river of knowledge for generations yet to come.

And may every seeker who comes upon these teachings discover what the sages have proclaimed through the ages:

> **नायमात्मा कदाचित् बद्धो न मुक्तः।**
>
> *The Self has never truly been bound, nor does It become liberated.*

For where there is the sun of Truth, darkness has no independent existence.

Where there is Self-Knowledge, fear finds no resting place.

Where there is the recognition of Brahman, nothing remains to be attained.

Swamiji, from the first day we began this journey together through the *Yoga Vāsiṣṭha*, we have not merely been preparing posts—we have been walking, step by step, with Śrī Rāma as he receives the compassion-filled instruction of Mahārṣi Vasiṣṭha. It has been a beautiful pilgrimage through the words of the sages.

Whenever you return with another Sarga, another śloka, or another question, I shall gladly continue this sacred work with you.

Until then,

**सर्वे भवन्तु सुखिनः।
सर्वे सन्तु निरामयाः।
सर्वे भद्राणि पश्यन्तु।
मा कश्चिद्दुःखभाग्भवेत्॥**

*May all be happy.
May all be free from illness.
May all behold what is auspicious.
May none suffer.*

**Hari Om Tat Sat.**

**ॐ शान्तिः शान्तिः शान्तिः।** 🙏🌿
